author: cmpilato
msg: Empower (woohoo!) `svn up' to replace missing items by name.  Most of
this change involves patches submitted by Kevin Pilch-Bisson.
Patch by: Kevin Pilch-Bisson
(Tweaked by me.)
* libsvn_wc/get_editor.c
* include/svn_wc.h
(svn_wc_get_actual_target): Renamed arguments PARENT_DIR and ENTRY
to ANCHOR and TARGET respectively.  Docstring rewrites, too.
* libsvn_wc/adm_crawler.c
(svn_wc_crawl_revisions): Make this function not freak out when
reporting missing items from a working copy.
* libsvn_repos/delta.c
(svn_repos_dir_delta): If the source path is missing from its root,
rebuild it using the target as a model.
* libsvn_client/update.c
(svn_client_update): Keep update from puking when being asked to
update items missing from the working copy by name.
* tests/clients/cmdline/basic_tests.py
(update_missing): New test for updating files missing from the
working copy.

author: joe
msg: Only support https: URLs if neon is compiled with SSL support.
* configure.in: Add macros neon exports to CFLAGS.
* subversion/libsvn_ra_dav/session.c (svn_ra_dav_init): Only advertise
support for "https" schema if NEON_SSL is defined.

author: joe
msg: * ra_loader.c: s/index/idx/g to fix compiler warning on Linux.

author: brane
msg: Just playing around.
